message.content:
cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enhancing data privacy and security.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of managing data by third parties and proposes a committee of independent nodes to govern access to the data capsule.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a self-expiring data capsule and discusses the access policy and expiring condition associated with it.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper proposes a framework called TEEKAP and discusses its implementation and empirical experiments.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the integration of hardware primitive and state machine replication in the design of the self-expiring data encapsulation framework.
